A section of the new multimillion-rand university library that is being built by three Eastern Cape universities collapsed on the weekend. &nbsp;The University of Fort Hare (UFH) yesterday [SUBS: MON] confirmed that a small portion of brickwork had collapsed in the collaborative library for 18000 students which is which is under construction in East London s Church Street.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions.&nbsp;